s have a formula or quasi-formula handy for predicting (relative) dps of weapons?<br>
<br>
as an example:<br>
Windblade: 50/44 15AC Bonus 43 at level 64(my level)<br>
War Marshall's Bladed Staff: 31/28 Bonus 33 at level 64<br>
<br>
If I had both weapons (or some other weapon I'm looking at) I could, of course parse them and find out for myself. But barring that, are there any formulas that are somewhat reliable? I remember a couple of apps people had written in the past, but that was long before the changed to damage tables, bonuses, etc.<br>
<br>
Thanks  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lythe@thesteelwarrior>Lythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 4:08:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4956.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmmmm</span><hr size=1> Well, if you want the comparison (as opposed to the absolute DPS), for 2 2handers its just:<br>
<br>
rating = avg hit / delay = (bonus + c*damage)/delay<br>
<br>
Now,  the thing is,  the mitigation constant &quot;c&quot; could vary from 1.1 vs Luclin named with no atk buffs, up to 3.2+ with avatar + rangerbuffs etc... Easiest way to find &quot;c&quot; is to parse your *average hit* (with any weapon, but if DWing don't have same type in each hand <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) and solve for &quot;c&quot;.  You can now predict your damage with any weapon vs that mob.<br>
<br>
If you want to compare 1handers to 2handers you need to look at Dual wield success rates and main hand triple attack rates as well (but not double attack,  common factor between both so cancels), but its fairly safe to say DPSwise that good 2handers &gt; good 1handers anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Rough example:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->  Mitigation constants won't be far off, but right way to do it is to parse your average hit with any weapon and solve for it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">L64 slapping PoP exp mobs with primal procced.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Windblade rating ~ (50*3.1 + 43)/44 = 4.5<br>
Staff rating ~ (31*3.1 + 33)/28 = 4.61  (2.5% better)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Or slapping Any_Luclin_Boss with no avatar/rangerbuffs</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
Windblade rating ~ (50*1.25 + 43)/44 = 2.39<br>
Staff rating ~ (31*1.25 + 33)/28 = 2.56 (7.1% better)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Lythe<br>
<br>
[EDIT:]  If one assumed triple attack fires 10% of the time and dual wield 75% of the time (not exact numbers probably,  but unlikely to be far off,  again,  get these weapon independent constants for YOUR AA/level/class by parsing it.  Punishing blade or ambi for example would change the 1hander/2hander comparison alot. ),  DWing a 15/20 + 13/20 would rate (on the same scale as above, hence the overall 1.1 divisor) at:<br>
<br>
(Avatar. EXP): <br>
(1.1*(15*3.1 + 13)/20 + 0.75*(13*3.1)/20) / 1.1 =  4.34 (couple of percent behind windblade)<br>
<br>
(No Avatar, Luclin Boss):<br>
(1.1*(15*1.25 + 13)/20 + 0.75*(13*1.25)/20) / 1.1 =  2.14 (Completely Owned,  staff does 20% more damage)<br>
